================================================================================
TIER III — THE SOVEREIGN LAYER (The Global Mandate)
================================================================================

This tier governs the Mission and the 17 SDG Nodes. It is a binding addendum
that applies to all use of this software regardless of the applicable code or
asset license tier.

§1 THE MANDATE

This software is a tool aligned with the United Nations Sustainable Development
Goals (UN SDGs). Any natural person, legal entity, corporation, government body,
or other organisation (collectively "Entity") using this code to:

  (a) actively work against or subvert any of the 17 UN SDGs, or
  (b) exploit, harm, or extract value from the "40%" — defined as the
      portion of the global population experiencing systemic disadvantage
      due to poverty, discrimination, conflict, or lack of access to basic
      services —

immediately and automatically forfeits all rights granted under Tiers I and II
and must cease all use, distribution, and modification of this software.

§2 ANTI-RINSING PROVISION

"Rinsing" is defined as the commercial extraction of value from this software
without contributing equivalent value back to the communities the software
is designed to serve.

  (a) Any Entity with annual revenue or funding exceeding USD $1,000,000 (one
      million US dollars) in the 12-month period preceding their use of
      Lilieth-patented Node logic MUST satisfy ONE of the following conditions
      to continue using the Lilieth-patented Node logic:

      (i)  Contribute to the Sovereign Shield Fund at a rate published by the
           LILIETH-PULSE project at the time of use; OR

      (ii) Submit a verified "Proof of Impact" report demonstrating direct,
           measurable benefit delivered to SDG-aligned communities through
           use of this software.

  (b) Failure to satisfy §2(a) within 90 days of crossing the revenue
      threshold constitutes a material breach of this license and immediately
      and automatically terminates all rights granted under all three tiers.

§3 ENFORCEMENT

  (a) The LILIETH-PULSE project maintainers and any affected community
      stakeholder may bring an action to enforce this license.

  (b) Nothing in this tier limits the remedies available under Tier I (GPLv3)
      or Tier II (CC BY-NC 4.0).

  (c) If any provision of this tier is found unenforceable in a particular
      jurisdiction, the remaining provisions remain in full force and effect.

§4 NO WARRANTY

THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
IMPLIED. THE LILIETH-PULSE PROJECT AND ITS CONTRIBUTORS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE
FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING FROM, OUT OF, OR IN
CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.

